            "name": "the Mesorah (TaNaKh)",
            "bio": "The Mesorah (Heb: <span class=\"hebrew\">מָסוֹרָה</span>) a/k/a, the Masoretic text is the authoritative Hebrew and Aramaic text of the TaNaKh for Karaite and Rabbinic Judaism. It was primarily copied, edited and distributed by a group of Jews known as the Masoretes between the 7th and 10th centuries CE. The Masoretic Text defines the Jewish canon and its precise letter-text, with its vocalization and accentuation known as the Masorah.",
